18/12/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia -- A NATO military liaison office opened in Belgrade on Monday (December 18th), days after President Boris Tadic sealed the accord formalising Serbia's accession to the Partnership for Peace programme.
The office, located in the Defence Ministry building, is headed by French Brigadier General Yannick Asset.
One of the office's main objectives would be to assist with the reform and modernisation processes within the Serbian armed forces.
(B92, Beta - 18/12/06;
NATO website - 15/12/06)
